obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (42837)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 125
  title `"Contract of indemnity" defined`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=42837&sectionno=124&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `A contract by which one party promises to save the other`
  line `from loss caused to him by the conduct of the promisor himself, or by the conduct of any other person, is`
  line `called a contract of indemnity.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A contracts to indemnify B against the consequences of any proceedings which C may take against B in respect of a certain`
  line `sum of 200 rupees. This is a contract of indemnity.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (38681)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 126
  title `Rights of indemnity-holder when sued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38681&sectionno=125&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `The promise in a contract of indemnity, acting`
  line `within the scope of his authority, is entitled to recover from the promisor—`
  line
  line `(1) all damages which he may be compelled to pay in any suit in respect of any matter to which`
  line `the promise to indemnify applies;`
  line
  line `(2) all costs which he may be compelled to pay in any such suit if, in bringing or defending it, he`
  line `did not contravene the orders of the promisor, and acted as it would have been prudent for him to act`
  line `in the absence of any contract of indemnity, or if the promisor authorized him to bring or defend the`
  line suit;
  line
  line `(3) all sums which he may have paid under the terms of any compromise of any such suit, if the`
  line `compromise was not contrary to the orders of the promisor, and was one which it would have been`
  line `prudent for the promisee to make in the absence of any contract of indemnity, or if the promisor`
  line `authorized him to compromise the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (38682)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 127
  title `"Contract of guarantee", "surety", "principal debtor" and "creditor".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38682&sectionno=126&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `A "contract of`
  line `guarantee" is a contract to perform the promise, or discharge the liability, of a third person in case of his`
  line `default. The person who gives the guarantee is called the "surety"; the person in respect of whose default`
  line `the guarantee is given is called the "principal debtor", and the person to whom the guarantee is given is`
  line `called the "creditor". A guarantee may be either oral or written.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (38683)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 128
  title `Consideration for guarantee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38683&sectionno=127&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Anything done, or any promise made, for the benefit of the`
  line `principal debtor, may be a sufficient consideration to the surety for giving the guarantee.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) B requests A to sell and deliver to him goods on credit. A agrees to do so, provided C will guarantee the payment of the`
  line `price of the goods. C promises to guarantee the payment in consideration of A's promise to deliver the goods. This is a sufficient`
  line `consideration for C's promise.`
  line
  line `(b) A sells and delivers goods to B. C afterwards requests A to forbear to sue B for the debt for a year, and promises that, if`
  line `he does so, C will pay for them in default of payment by B. A agrees to forbear as requested. This is a sufficient consideration for`
  line `C's promise.`
  line
  line `(c) A sells and delivers goods to B. C afterwards, without consideration, agrees to pay for them in default of B. The`
  line `agreement is void.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (38684)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 129
  title `Surety's liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38684&sectionno=128&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `The liability of the surety is co- extensive with that of the principal debtor,`
  line `unless it is otherwise provided by the contract.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A guarantees to B the payment of a bill of exchange by C, the acceptor. The bill is dishonoured by C. A is liable, not only`
  line `for the amount of the bill, but also for any interest and charges which may have become due on it.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (38685)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 130
  title `"Continuing guarantee".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38685&sectionno=129&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `A guarantee which extends to a series of transactions, is called a`
  line `"continuing guarantee".`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, in consideration that B will employ C in collecting the rent of B's zamindari, promises B to be responsible, to the`
  line `amount of 5,000 rupees, for the due collection and payment by C of those rents. This is a continuing guarantee.`
  line
  line `(b) A guarantees payment to B, a tea-dealer, to the amount of £ 100, for any tea he may from time to time supply to C. B`
  line `supplies C with tea to above the value of £ 100, and C pays B for it. Afterwards, B supplies C with tea to the value of £ 200. C`
  line `fails to pay. The guarantee given by A was a continuing guarantee, and he is accordingly liable to B to the extent of £ 100.`
  line
  line `(c) A guarantees payment to B of the price of five sacks of flour to be delivered by B to C and to be paid for in a month. B`
  line `delivers five sacks to C. C pays for them. Afterwards B delivers four sacks to C, which C does riot pay for. The guarantee given`
  line `by A was not a continuing guarantee, and accordingly he is not liable for the price of the four sacks.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (38686)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 131
  title `Revocation of continuing guarantee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38686&sectionno=130&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `A continuing guarantee may at any time be revoked by`
  line `the surety, as to future transactions, by notice to the creditor.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, in consideration of B's discounting, at As request, bills of exchange for C, guarantees to B, for twelve months, the`
  line `due payment of all such bills to the extent of 5,000 rupees. B discounts bills for C to the extent of 2,000 rupees. Afterwards, at the`
  line `end of three months, A revokes the guarantee. This revocation discharges A from all liability to B for any subsequent discount.`
  line `But A is liable to B for the 2,000 rupees, on default of C.`
  line
  line `(b) A guarantees to B, to the extent of 10,000 rupees, that C shall pay all the bills that B shall draw upon him. B draws upon`
  line `C. C accepts the bill. A gives notice of revocation. C dishonours the bill at maturity. A is liable upon his guarantee.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (38687)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 132
  title `Revocation of continuing guarantee by surety's death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38687&sectionno=131&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `The death of the surety operates, in`
  line `the absence of any contract to the contrary, as a revocation of a continuing guarantee, so far as regards`
  line `future transactions.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (42838)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 133
  title `Liability of two persons, primarily liable, not affected by arrangement between them that one shall be surety on others default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=42838&sectionno=132&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `Where two persons contract with a third person to undertake a`
  line `certain liability, and also contract with each other that one of them shall be liable only on the default of`
  line `the other, the third person not being a party to such contract, the liability of each of such two persons to`
  line `the third person under the first contract is not affected by the existence of the second contract, although`
  line `such third person may have been aware of its existence.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A and B make a joint and several promissory note to C. A makes it, in fact, as surety for B, and C knows this at the time`
  line `when the note is made. The fact that A, to the knowledge of C, made the note as surety for B, is no answer to a suit by C against`
  line `A upon the note.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (38689)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 134
  title `Discharge of surety by variance in terms of contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1917, s. 2 and the first Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38689&sectionno=133&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `Any variance, made without the`
  line `suretys consent, in the terms of the contract between the principal ^1`
  line `[debtor] and the creditor, discharges`
  line `the surety as to transactions subsequent to the variance.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A becomes surety to C for B's conduct as a manager in C's bank. Afterwards, B and C contract, without A's consent,`
  line `that B's salary shall be raised, and that he shall become liable for one-fourth of the losses on overdrafts. B allows a customer to`
  line `overdraw, and the bank loses a sum of money. A is discharged from his suretyship by the variance made without his consent, and`
  line `is not liable to make good this loss.`
  line
  line `(b) A guarantees C against the misconduct of B in an office to which B is appointed by C, and of which the duties are`
  line `defined by an Act of the Legislature. By a subsequent Act, the nature of the office is materially altered. Afterwards, B`
  line `misconducts himself. A is discharged by the change from future liability under his guarantee, though the misconduct of B is in`
  line `respect of a duty not affected by the later Act.`
  line
  line `(c) C agrees to appoint B as his clerk to sell goods at a yearly salary, upon A's becoming surety to C for B's duly accounting`
  line `for moneys received by him as such clerk. Afterwards, without As knowledge or consent, C and B agree that B should be paid`
  line `by a commission on the goods sold by him and not by a fixed salary. A is not liable for subsequent misconduct of B.`
  line
  line `(d) A gives to C a continuing guarantee to the extent of 3,000 rupees for any oil supplied by C to B on credit. Afterwards B`
  line `becomes embarrassed, and, without the knowledge of A, B and C contract that C shall continue to supply B with oil for ready`
  line `money, and that the payments shall be applied to the then, existing debts between B and C. A is not liable on his guarantee for`
  line `any goods supplied after: this new arrangement.`
  line
  line `(e) C contracts to lend B 5,000 rupees on the 1st March. A guarantees repayment. C pays the 5,000 rupees to B on the 1st`
  line `January. A is discharged from his liability, as the contract has been varied, inasmuch as C might sue B for the money before the`
  line `1st of March.`
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (38690)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 135
  title `Discharge of surety by release or discharge of principal debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38690&sectionno=134&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `The surety is discharged`
  line `by any contract between the creditor and the principal debtor, by which the principal debtor is released, or`
  line `by any act or omission of the creditor, the legal consequence of which is the discharge of the principal`
  line debtor.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A gives a guarantee to C for goods to be supplied by C to B. C supplies goods to B, and afterwards B becomes`
  line `embarrassed and contracts with his creditors (including C) to assign to them his property in consideration of their releasing him`
  line `from their demands. Here B is released from his debt by the contract with C, and A is discharged from his suretyship.`
  line
  line `(b) A contracts with B to grow a crop of indigo on A's land and to deliver it to B at a fixed rate, and C guarantees A's`
  line `performance of this contract. B diverts a stream of water which is necessary for the irrigation of A's land and thereby prevents`
  line `him from raising the indigo. C is no longer liable on his guarantee.`
  line
  line `(c) A contracts with B for a fixed price to build a house for B within a stipulated time, B supplying the necessary timber. C`
  line `guarantees A's performance of the contract. B omits to supply the timber. C is discharged from his suretyship.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (42839)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 136
  title `Discharge of surety when creditor compounds with, gives time to, or agrees not to sue, principal debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=42839&sectionno=135&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `A contract between the creditor and the principal debtor, by which the creditor makes`
  line `a composition with, or promises to give time to, or not to sue, the principal debtor, discharges the surety,`
  line `unless the surety assents to such contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (38692)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 137
  title `Surety not discharged when agreement made with third person to give time to principal debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38692&sectionno=136&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `Where a contract to give time to the principal debtor is made by the creditor with a third`
  line `person, and not with the principal debtor, the surety is not discharged.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `C, the holder of an overdue bill of exchange drawn by A as surety for B, and accepted by B, contracts with M to give time to`
  line `B. A is not discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (38693)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 138
  title `Creditor's forbearance to sue does not discharge surety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38693&sectionno=137&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `Mere forbearance on the part of`
  line `the creditor to sue the principal debtor or to enforce any other remedy against him does not, in the absence`
  line `of any provision in the guarantee to the contrary, discharge the surety.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `B owes to C a debt guaranteed by A. The debt becomes payable. C does not sue B for a year after the debt has become`
  line `payable. A is not discharged from his suretyship.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (38694)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 139
  title `Release of one co-surety does not discharge others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes `1. See s. 44, supra.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38694&sectionno=138&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `Where there are co-sureties, a release by`
  line `the creditor of one of them does not discharge the others; neither does it free the surety so released from`
  line `his responsibility to the other sureties^1`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (38695)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 140
  title `Discharge of surety of creditor's act or omission impairing surety's eventual remedy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38695&sectionno=139&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line If
  line `the creditor does any act which is inconsistent with the rights of the surety, or omits to do any act which`
  line `his duty to the surety requires him to do, and the eventual remedy of the surety himself against the`
  line `principal debtor is thereby impaired, the surety is discharged.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) B contracts to build a ship for C for a given sum, to be paid by instalments as the work reaches certain stages. A becomes`
  line `surety to C for B's due performance of the contract. C, without the knowledge of A, prepays to B the last two instalments. A is`
  line `discharged by this prepayment.`
  line
  line `(b) C lends money to B on the security of a joint and several promissory note made in C's favour by B, and by A as surety`
  line `for B, together with a bill of sale of B's furniture, which gives power to C to sell the furniture, and apply the proceeds in`
  line `discharge of the note. Subsequently, C sells the furniture, but, owing to his misconduct and wilful negligence, only a small price`
  line `is realized. A is discharged from liability on the note.`
  line
  line `(c) A puts M as apprentice to B, and gives a guarantee to B for M's fidelity. B promises on his part that he will, at least once`
  line `a month, see M make up the cash. B omits to see this done as promised, and M embezzles. A is not liable to B on his guarantee.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (38696)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 141
  title `Rights of surety on payment or performance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38696&sectionno=140&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `Where a guaranteed debt has become due, or`
  line `default of the principal debtor to perform a guaranteed duty has taken place, the surety upon payment or`
  line `performance of all that he is liable for, is invested with all the rights which the creditor had against the`
  line `principal debtor.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (38697)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 142
  title `Surety's right to benefit of creditor's securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38697&sectionno=141&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `A surety is entitled to the benefit of every`
  line `security which the creditor has against the principal debtor at the time when the contract of suretyship is`
  line `entered into, whether the surety knows of the existence of such security or not; and if the creditor loses,`
  line `or, without the consent of the surety, parts with such security, the surety is discharged to the extent of the`
  line `value of the security.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) C, advances to B, his tenant, 2,000 rupees on the guarantee of A. C has also a further security for the 2,000 rupees by a`
  line `mortgage of B's furniture. C cancels the mortgage. B becomes insolvent and C sues A on his guarantee. A is discharged from`
  line `liability to the amount of the value of the furniture.`
  line
  line `(b) C, a creditor, whose advance to B is secured by a decree, receives also a guarantee for that advance from A. C afterwards`
  line `takes B's goods in execution under the decree, and then, without the knowledge of A, withdraws the execution. A is discharged.`
  line
  line `(c) A, as surety for B, makes a bond jointly with B to C, to secure a loan from C to B. Afterwards, C obtains from B a`
  line `further security for the same debt. Subsequently, C gives up the further security. A is not discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (38698)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 143
  title `Guarantee obtained by misrepresentation invalid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38698&sectionno=142&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `Any guarantee which has been obtained`
  line `by means of misrepresentation made by the creditor, or with his knowledge and assent, concerning a`
  line `material part of the transaction, is invalid.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (38699)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 144
  title `Guarantee obtained by concealment invalid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38699&sectionno=143&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `Any guarantee which the creditor has obtained`
  line `by means of keeping silence as to material circumstances, is invalid.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A engages B as clerk to collect money for him. B fails to account for some of his receipts, and A in consequence calls`
  line `upon him to furnish security for his duly accounting. C gives his guarantee for B's duly accounting. A does not acquaint C with`
  line `B's previous conduct. B afterwards makes default. The guarantee is invalid.`
  line
  line `(b) A guarantees to C payment for iron to be supplied by him to B to the amount of 2,000 tons. B and C have privately`
  line `agreed that B should pay five rupees per ton beyond the market price, such excess to be applied in liquidation of an old debt. This`
  line `agreement is concealed from A. A is not liable as a surety.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (38700)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 145
  title `Guarantee on contract that creditor shall not act on it until co-surety joins.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38700&sectionno=144&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `Where a`
  line `person gives a guarantee upon a contract that the creditor shall not act upon it until another person has`
  line `joined in it as co-surety, the guarantee is not valid if that other person does not join.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (38701)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 146
  title `Implied promise to indemnify surety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38701&sectionno=145&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `In every contract of guarantee there is an implied`
  line `promise by the principal debtor to indemnify the surety, and the surety is entitled to recover from the`
  line `principal debtor whatever sum he has rightfully paid under the guarantee, but, no sums which he has paid`
  line wrongfully.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) B is indebted to C, and A is surety for the debt. C demands payment from A, and on his refusal sues him for the amount.`
  line `A defends the suit, having reasonable grounds for doing so, but is compelled to pay the amount of the debt with costs. He can`
  line `recover from B the amount paid by him for costs, as well as the principal debt.`
  line
  line `(b) C lends B a sum of money, and A, at the request of B, accepts a bill of exchange drawn by B upon A to secure the`
  line `amount. C, the holder of the bill, demands payment of it from A, and, on A's refusal to pay, sues him upon the bill. A, not having`
  line `reasonable grounds for so doing, defends the suit, and has to pay the amount of the bill and costs. He can recover from B the`
  line `amount of the bill, but not the sum paid for costs, as there was no real ground for defending the action.`
  line
  line `(c) A guarantees to C, to the extent of 2,000 rupees, payment for rice to be supplied by C to B. C supplies to B rice to a less`
  line `amount than 2,000 rupees, but obtains from A payment of the sum of 2,000 rupees in respect of the rice supplied. A cannot`
  line `recover from B more than the price of the rice actually supplied.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (38702)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 147
  title `Co-sureties liable to contribute equally.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes `1. See s. 43, supra.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38702&sectionno=146&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `Where two or more persons are co-sureties for the`
  line `same debt or duty, either jointly or severally, and whether under the same or different contracts, and`
  line `whether with or without the knowledge of each other, the co-sureties, in the absence of any contract to the`
  line `contrary, are liable, as between themselves, to pay each an equal share of the whole debt, or of that part of`
  line `it which remains unpaid by the principal debtor^1`
  line .
  line
  line Illustrationsbr
  line
  line `(a) A, B and C are sureties to D for the sum of 3,000 rupees lent to E. E makes default in payment. A, B and C are liable, as`
  line `between themselves, to pay 1,000 rupees each.`
  line
  line `(b) A, B and C are sureties to D for the sum of 1,000 rupees lent to E, and there is a contract between A, B and C that A is to`
  line `be responsible to the extent of one-quarter, B to the extent of one- quarter, and C to the extent of one-half. E makes default in`
  line `payment. As between the sureties, A is liable to pay 250 rupees, B 250 rupees, and C 500 rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (38703)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 148
  title `Liability of co-sureties bound in different sums.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38703&sectionno=147&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `Co-sureties who are bound in different sums`
  line `are liable to pay equally as far as the limits of their respective obligations permit.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, B and C, as sureties for D, enter into three several bonds, each in a different penalty, namely, A in the penalty of each`
  line `10,000 rupees, B in that of 20,000 rupees, C in that of 40,000 rupees, conditioned for D's duly accounting to E. D makes default`
  line `to the extent of 30,000 rupees. A, B and C are each liable to pay 10,000 rupees.`
  line
  line `(b) A, B and C, as sureties for D, enter into three several bonds, each in a different penalty, namely, A in the penalty of`
  line `10,000 rupees, B in that of 20,000 rupees, C in that of 40,000 rupees, conditioned for D's duly accounting to E. D makes default`
  line `to the extent of 40,000 rupees. A is liable to pay 10,000 rupees, and B and C 15,000 rupees each.`
  line
  line `(c) A, B and C, as sureties for D, enter into three several bonds, each in a different penalty, namely, A in the penalty of`
  line `10,000 rupees, B in that of 20,000 rupees, C in that of 40,000 rupees, conditioned for D's duly accounting to E. D makes default`
  line `to the extent of 70,000 rupees. A, B and C have to pay each the full penalty of his bond.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (38704)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 149
  title `"Bailment", "bailor" and "bailee" defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38704&sectionno=148&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `A "bailment" is the delivery of goods by one`
  line `person to another for some purpose, upon a contract that they shall, when the purpose is accomplished, be`
  line `returned or otherwise disposed of according to the directions of the person delivering them. The person`
  line `delivering the goods is called the "bailor". The person to whom they are delivered is called, the "bailee".`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If a person already in possession of the goods of another contracts to hold them as a`
  line `bailee, he thereby becomes the bailee, and the owner becomes the bailor of such goods, although they`
  line `may not have been delivered by way of bailment`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (38705)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 150
  title `Delivery to bailee how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38705&sectionno=149&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `The delivery to the bailee may be made by doing anything`
  line `which has the effect of putting the goods in the possession of the intended bailee or of any person`
  line `authorized to hold them on his behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (38706)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 151
  title `Bailor's duty to disclose faults in goods bailed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38706&sectionno=150&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `The bailor is bound to disclose to the bailee`
  line `faults in the goods bailed, of which the bailor is aware, and which materially interfere with the use of`
  line `them, or expose the bailee to extraordinary risks; and if he does not make such disclosure, he is`
  line `responsible for damage arising to the bailee directly from such faults.`
  line
  line `If the goods are bailed for hire, the bailor is responsible for such damage, whether he was or was not`
  line `aware of the existence of such faults in the goods bailed.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A lends a horse, which he knows to be vicious, to B. He does not disclose the fact that the horse is vicious. The horse`
  line `runs away. B is thrown and injured. A is responsible to B for damage sustained.`
  line
  line `(b) A hires a carriage of B. The carriage is unsafe, though B is not aware of it, and A is injured. B is responsible to A for the`
  line injury.
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (38707)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 152
  title `Care to be taken by bailee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38707&sectionno=151&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `^1In all cases of bailment the bailee is bound to take as much care`
  line `of the goods bailed to him as a man of ordinary prudence would, under similar circumstances, take of his`
  line `own goods of the same bulk, quality and value as the goods bailed^2`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The responsibility of the Trustees of the Port of Madras constituted under the Madras Port Trust Act, 1905 (Madras Act`
  line `2 of 1905), in regard to goods has been declared to be that of a bailee under these sections, without the qualifying words "in the`
  line `absence of any special contract" in s. 152, see s. 40(1) of that Act.`
  line
  line `2. As to railway contracts see the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890), s. 72. As to the liability of common carriers, see the`
  line `Carriers Act, 1865 (3 of 1865), s. 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (38708)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 153
  title `Bailee when not liable for loss, etc., of thing bailed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38708&sectionno=152&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `The bailee, in the absence of any special`
  line `contract, is not responsible for the loss, destruction or deterioration of the thing bailed, if he has taken the`
  line `amount of care of it described in section 151.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (38709)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 154
  title `Termination of bailment by bailee's act inconsistent with conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38709&sectionno=153&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `A contract of`
  line `bailment is avoidable at the option of the bailor, if the bailee does any act with regard to the goods bailed,`
  line `inconsistent with the conditions of the bailment.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A lets to B, for hire, a horse for his own riding. B drives the horse in his carriage. This is, at the 'option of A, a termination`
  line `of the bailment.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (38710)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 155
  title `Liability of bailee making unauthorized use of goods bailed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38710&sectionno=154&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `If the bailee makes any use of`
  line `the goods bailed which is not according to the conditions of the bailment, he is liable to make`
  line `compensation to the bailor for any damage arising to the goods from or during such use of them.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A lends a horse to B for his own riding only. B allows C, a member of his family, to ride the horse. C rides with care, but`
  line `the horse accidentally falls and is injured. B is liable to make compensation to A for the injury done to the horse.`
  line
  line `(b) A hires a horse in Calcutta from B expressly to march to Benares. A rides with clue care, but marches to Cuttack instead.`
  line `The horse accidentally falls and is injured. A is liable to make compensation to B for the injury to the horse.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (38711)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 156
  title `Effect of mixture, with bailor's consent, of his goods with bailee's.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38711&sectionno=155&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `If the bailee, with the`
  line `consent of the bailor, mixes the goods of the bailor with his own goods, the bailor and the bailee shall`
  line `have an interest, in proportion to their respective shares, in the mixture thus produced.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (38712)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 157
  title `Effect of mixture, without bailor's consent, when the good can be separated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38712&sectionno=156&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `If the bailee,`
  line `without the consent of the bailor, mixes the goods of the bailor with his own goods, and the goods can be`
  line `separated or divided, the property in the goods remains in the parties respectively; but the bailee is bound`
  line `to bear the expense of separation or division, and any damage arising from the mixture.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bails 100 bales of cotton marked with a particular mark to B. B, without A's consent, mixes the 100 bales with other bales`
  line `of his own, bearing a different mark: A is entitled to have his 100 bales returned, and B is bound to bear all the expense incurred`
  line `in the separation of the bales, and any other incidental damage.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (38713)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 158
  title `Effect of mixture, without bailor's consent, when the goods cannot be separated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38713&sectionno=157&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `bailee, without the consent of the bailor, mixes the goods of the bailor with his own goods, in such a`
  line `manner that it is impossible to separate the goods bailed from the other goods, and deliver them back, the`
  line `bailor is entitled to be compensated by the bailee for the loss of the goods.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bails a barrel of Cape flour worth Rs. 45 to B. B, without A's consent, mixes the flour with country flour of his own,`
  line `worth only Rs. 25 a barrel. B must compensate A for the loss of his flour.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (38714)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 159
  title `Repayment, by bailor, of necessary expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38714&sectionno=158&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Where, by the conditions of the bailment, the`
  line `goods are to be kept or to be carried, or to have work done upon them by the bailee for the bailor, and the`
  line `bailee is to receive no remuneration, the bailor shall repay to the bailee the necessary expenses incurred`
  line `by him for the purpose of the bailment.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (38715)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 160
  title `Restoration of goods lent gratuitously.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38715&sectionno=159&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `The lender of a thing for use may at any time require`
  line `its return, if the loan was gratuitous, even though he lent it for a specified time or purpose. But if, on the`
  line `faith of such loan made for a specified time or purpose, the borrower has acted in such a manner that the`
  line `return of the thing lent before the time agreed upon would cause him loss exceeding the benefit actually`
  line `derived by him from the loan, the lender must, if he compels the return, indemnify the borrower for the`
  line `amount in which the loss so occasioned exceeds the benefit so derived.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (38716)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 161
  title `Return of goods bailed, on expiration of time or accomplishment of purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38716&sectionno=160&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `It is the duty`
  line `of the bailee to return, or deliver according to the bailors directions, the goods bailed, without demand, as`
  line `soon as the time for which they were bailed has expired, or the purpose for which they were bailed has`
  line `been accomplished.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (38717)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 162
  title `Bailee's responsibility when goods are not duly returned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38717&sectionno=161&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `^1If, by the default of the bailee,`
  line `the goods are not returned, delivered or tendered at the proper time, he is responsible to the bailor for any`
  line `loss, destruction or deterioration of the goods from that time.^2`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 161 has been, declared to apply to the responsibility of the Trustees of the Port of Madras as to goods in their possession see`
  line `the Madras Port Trust Act, 1905 (Madras Act 2 of 1905).`
  line
  line `2. As to Railway contracts, see the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890), s. 72.`
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (38718)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 163
  title `Termination of gratuitous bailment by death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38718&sectionno=162&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `A gratuitous bailment is terminated by the`
  line `death either of the bailor or of the bailee.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (38719)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 164
  title `Bailor entitled to increase or profit from goods bailed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38719&sectionno=163&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of any contract to the`
  line `contrary, the bailee is bound to deliver to the bailor, or according to his directions, any increase or profit`
  line `which may have accrued from the goods bailed.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A leaves a cow in the custody of B to be taken care of. The cow has a calf. B is bound to deliver the calf as well as the cow`
  line `to A.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (38720)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 165
  title `Bailor's responsibility to bailee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38720&sectionno=164&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `The bailor is responsible to the bailee for any loss which the`
  line `bailee may sustain by reason that the bailor was not entitled to make the bailment, or to receive back the`
  line `goods, or to give directions respecting them.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (38721)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 166
  title `Bailment by several joint owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38721&sectionno=165&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `If several joint owners of goods bail them, the bailee may`
  line `deliver them back to, or according to the directions of, one joint owner without the consent of all in the`
  line `absence of any agreement to the contrary.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (38722)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 167
  title `Bailee not responsible on re-delivery to bailor without title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes `1. See the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), s. 117.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38722&sectionno=166&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `If the bailor has no title to the`
  line `goods, and the bailee, in good faith, delivers them back to, or according to the directions of, the bailor, the`
  line `bailee is not responsible to the owner in respect of such delivery^1`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (38723)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 168
  title `Right of third person claiming goods bailed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38723&sectionno=167&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `If a person, other than the bailor, claims goods`
  line `bailed he may apply to the Court to stop the delivery of the goods to the bailor, and to decide the title to`
  line `the goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (38724)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 169
  title `Right of finder of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38724&sectionno=168&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `The finder of goods has no`
  line `right to sue the owner for compensation for trouble and expense voluntarily incurred by him to preserve`
  line `the goods and to find out the owner; but he may retain the goods against the owner until he receives such`
  line `compensation; and, where the owner has offered a specific reward for the return of goods lost, the finder`
  line `may sue for such reward, and may retain the goods until he receives it.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (38725)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 170
  title `When finder of thing commonly on sale may sell it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38725&sectionno=169&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `When a thing which is commonly the`
  line `subject of sale is lost, if the owner cannot with reasonable diligence be found, or if he refuses, upon`
  line `demand, to pay the lawful charges of the finder, the finder may sell it—`
  line
  line `(1) when the thing is in danger of perishing or of losing the greater part of its value, or,`
  line
  line `(2) when the lawful charges of the finder, in respect of the thing found, amount to two-thirds of`
  line `its value.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (38726)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 171
  title `Bailee's particular lien.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38726&sectionno=170&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `Where the bailee has, in accordance with the purpose of the`
  line `bailment, rendered any service involving the exercise of labour or skill in respect of the goods bailed, he`
  line `has, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, a right to retain such goods until he receives due`
  line `remuneration for the services he has rendered in respect of them.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A delivers a rough diamond to B, a jeweller, to be cut and polished, which is accordingly done. B is entitled to retain the`
  line `stone till he is paid for the services he has rendered.`
  line
  line `(b) A gives, cloth to B, a tailor, to make into a coat. B promises A to deliver the coat as soon as it is finished, and to give a`
  line `three months' credit for the price. B is not entitled to retain the coat until he is paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (38727)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 172
  title `General lien of bankers, factors, wharfingers, attorneys and policy-brokers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38727&sectionno=171&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line Bankers,
  line `factors, wharfingers, attorneys of a High Court and policy-brokers may, in the absence of a contract to the`
  line `contrary, retain as a security for a general balance of account, any goods bailed to them; but no other`
  line `persons have a right to retain, as a security for such balance, goods bailed to them, unless there is an`
  line `express contract to that effect^1`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. As to lien of an agent, see s. 221, infra. As to lien of a Railway Administration, see the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890),`
  line `s. 55.`
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (38728)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 173
  title `"Pledge", "Pawnor" and "Pawnee" defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38728&sectionno=172&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `The bailment of goods as security for payment`
  line `of a debt or performance of a promise is called "pledge". The bailor is in this case called the "pawnor".`
  line `The bailee is called the "pawnee".`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (38729)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 174
  title `Pawnee's right of retainer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38729&sectionno=173&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `The pawnee may retain the goods pledged, not only for payment`
  line `of the debt or the performance of the promise, but for the interest of the debt, and all necessary expenses`
  line `incurred by him in respect of the possession or for the preservation of the goods pledged.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (38730)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 175
  title `Pawnee not to retain for debt or promise other than that for which goods pledged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38730&sectionno=174&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `The pawnee shall not, in the absence of a contract to`
  line `that effect, retain the goods pledged for any debt or promise other than the debt or promise for which they`
  line `are pledged; but such contract, in the absence of anything to the contrary, shall be presumed in regard to`
  line `subsequent advances made by the pawnee.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (38731)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 176
  title `Pawnee's right as to extraordinary expenses incurred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38731&sectionno=175&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `The pawnee is entitled to receive`
  line `from the pawnor extraordinary expenses incurred by him for the preservation of the goods pledged.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (38732)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 177
  title `Pawnee's right where pawnor makes default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38732&sectionno=176&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `If the pawnor makes default in payment of the`
  line `debt, or performance, at the stipulated time of the promise, in respect of which the goods were pledged,`
  line `the pawnee may bring a suit against the pawnor upon the debt or promise, and retain the goods pledge as`
  line `a collateral security; or he may sell the thing pledged, on giving the pawnor reasonable notice of the sale.`
  line
  line `If the proceeds of such sale are less than the amount due in respect of the debt or promise, the pawnor`
  line `is still liable to pay the balance. If the proceeds of the sale are greater than the amount so due, the pawnee`
  line `shall pay over the surplus to the pawnor.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (38733)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 178
  title `Defaulting pawnor's right to redeem.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes `1. For limitation, see the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), the Second Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38733&sectionno=177&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `If a time is stipulated for the payment of the debt, of`
  line `performance of the promise, for which the pledge is made, and the pawnor makes default in payment of`
  line `the debt or performance of the promise at the stipulated time, he may redeem the goods pledged at any`
  line `subsequent time before the actual sale of them^1`
  line `; but he must, in that case, pay, in addition, any expenses`
  line `which have arisen from his default.`
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (38734)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 179
  title `Pledge by mercantile agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes `1. Ss. 178 and 178A subs. by Act 4 of 1930, s. 2, for the original s. 178.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38734&sectionno=178&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `^1Where a mercantile agent is, with the consent of the owner, in`
  line `possession of goods or the document of title to goods, any pledge made by him, when acting in the`
  line `ordinary course of business of a mercantile agent, shall be as valid as if he were expressly authorised by`
  line `the owner of the goods to make the same; provided that the pawnee acts in good faith and has not at the`
  line `time of the pledge notice that the pawnor has not authority to pledge.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section, the expressions mercantile agent and "documents of title" shall have`
  line `the meanings assigned to them in the Indian Sale of Goods Act, 1930 (3 of 1930).`
obj_root_law_sections_178_a:
  sectionId (38735)
  sectionNo 178A
  orderNo 180
  title `Pledge by person in possession under voidable contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38735&sectionno=178A&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_178_a_content:
  string
  line `When the pawnor has obtained`
  line `possession of the goods pledged by him under a contract voidable under section 19 or section 19A, but the contract has not been rescinded at the time of the pledge, the pawnee acquires a good title to the`
  line `goods, provided he acts in good faith and without notice of the pawnor's defect of title.]`
obj_root_law_sections_178_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (38736)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 181
  title `Pledge where pawnor has only a limited interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38736&sectionno=179&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `Where a person pledges goods in which`
  line `he has only a limited interest, the pledge is valid to the extent of that interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (38737)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 182
  title `Suit by bailor or bailee against wrong-doer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38737&sectionno=180&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `If a third person wrongfully deprives the bailee`
  line `of the use or possession of the goods bailed, or does them any injury, the bailee is entitled to use such`
  line `remedies as the owner might have used in the like case if no bailment had been made; and either the`
  line `bailor or the bailee may bring a suit against a third person for such deprivation or injury.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (38738)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 183
  title `Apportionment of relief or compensation obtained by such suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38738&sectionno=181&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `Whatever is obtained by`
  line `way of relief or compensation in any such suit shall, as between the bailor and the bailee, be dealt with`
  line `according to their respective interests.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (38739)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 184
  title `"Agent" and "principal" defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38739&sectionno=182&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `An "agent" is a person employed to do any act for another,`
  line `or to represent another in dealings with third persons. The person for whom such act is done, or who is so`
  line `represented, is called the "principal".`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (38740)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 185
  title `Who may employ agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38740&sectionno=183&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `Any person who is of the age of majority according to the law to`
  line `which he is subject, and who is of sound mind, may employ an agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (38741)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 186
  title `Who may be an agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38741&sectionno=184&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `As between the principal and third persons, any person may become`
  line `an agent, but no person who is not of the age of majority and of sound mind can become an agent, so as to`
  line `be responsible to his principal according to the provisions in that behalf herein contained.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (38742)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 187
  title `Consideration not necessary.`
  content `No consideration is necessary to create an agency.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38742&sectionno=185&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (38743)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 188
  title `Agent's authority may be expressed or implied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38743&sectionno=186&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `The authority of an agent may be expressed`
  line `or implied^1`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See, however, the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), s. 33; see also the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), Sch. I,`
  line `Order III, rule 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (38744)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 189
  title `Definitions of express and implied authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38744&sectionno=187&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `An authority is said to be express when it is`
  line `given by words spoken or written. An authority is said to be implied when it is to be inferred from the`
  line `circumstances of the case; and things spoken or written, or the ordinary course of dealing, may be`
  line `accounted circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A owns a shop in Serampore, living himself in Calcutta, and visiting the shop occasionally. The shop is managed by B, and`
  line `he is in the habit of ordering goods from C in the name of A for the purposes of the shop, and of paying for them out of A's funds`
  line `with A's knowledge. B has an implied authority from A to order goods from C in the name of A for the purposes of the shop`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (38745)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 190
  title `Extent of agent's authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38745&sectionno=188&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `An agent, having an authority to do an act, has authority to do`
  line `every lawful thing which is necessary in order to do such act.`
  line
  line `An agent having an authority to carry on a business, has authority to do every lawful thing necessary`
  line `for the purpose, or usually done in the course, of conducting such business.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A is employed by B, residing in London, to recover at Bombay a debt due to B. A may adopt any legal process necessary`
  line `for the purpose of recovering the debt, and may give a valid discharge for the same.`
  line
  line `(b) A constitutes B his agent to carry on his business of a shipbuilder. B may purchase timber and other materials, and hire`
  line `workmen, for the purpose of carrying on the business.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (38746)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 191
  title `Agent's authority in an emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38746&sectionno=189&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `An agent has authority, in an emergency, to do all such`
  line `acts for the purpose of protecting his principal from loss as would be done by a person of ordinary`
  line `prudence, in his own case, under similar circumstances.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) An agent for sale may have goods repaired if it be necessary.`
  line
  line `(b) A consigns provisions to B at Calcutta, with directions to send them immediately to C, at Cuttack. B may sell the`
  line `provisions at Calcutta, if they will not bear the journey to Cuttack without spoiling.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (38747)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 192
  title `When agent cannot delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38747&sectionno=190&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `An agent cannot lawfully employ another to perform acts`
  line `which he has expressly or impliedly undertaken to perform personally, unless by the ordinary custom of`
  line `trade a sub-agent may, or, from the nature of the agency, a sub-agent must, be employed.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (38748)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 193
  title `"Sub-agent" defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38748&sectionno=191&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `A "sub-agent" is a person employed by, and acting under the control of,`
  line `the original agent in the business of the agency.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (38749)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 194
  title `Representation of principal by sub-agent properly appointed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38749&sectionno=192&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `Where a sub-agent is`
  line `properly appointed, the principal is, so far as regards third persons, represented by the sub-agent, and is`
  line `bound by and responsible for his acts, as if he were an agent originally appointed by the principal.`
  line
  line `Agent's responsibility for sub-agent.—The agent is responsible to the principal for the acts of the`
  line sub-agent.
  line
  line `Sub-agent's responsibility.—The sub-agent is responsible for his acts to the agent, but not to the`
  line `principal, except in cases of fraud or wilful wrong.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (38750)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 195
  title `Agent's responsibility for sub-agent appointed without authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38750&sectionno=193&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `Where an agent, without`
  line `having authority to do so, has appointed a person to act as a sub-agent, the agent stands towards such`
  line `person in the relation of a principal to an agent, and is responsible for his acts both to the principal and to`
  line `third persons; the principal is not represented, by or responsible for the acts of the person so employed,`
  line `nor is that person responsible to the principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (38751)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 196
  title `Relation between principal and person duly appointed by agent to act in business of agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38751&sectionno=194&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `Where an agent, holding an express or implied authority to name another person to act for the`
  line `principal in the business of the agency, has named another person accordingly, such person is not a`
  line `sub-agent, but an agent of the principal for such part of the business of the agency as is entrusted to him.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A directs B, his solicitor, to sell his estate by auction, and to employ an auctioneer for the purpose. B names C, an`
  line `auctioneer, to conduct the sale. C is not a sub-agent, but is A's agent for the conduct of the sale.`
  line
  line `(b) A authorizes B, a merchant in Calcutta, to recover the moneys due to A from C & Co. B instructs D, a solicitor, to take`
  line `legal proceedings against C & Co. for the recovery of the money. D is not a sub-agent, but is solicitor for A.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (38752)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 197
  title `Agent's duty in naming such person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38752&sectionno=195&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `In selecting such agent for his principal, an agent is`
  line `bound to exercise the same amount of discretion as a man of ordinary prudence would exercise in his own`
  line `case; and, if he does this, he is not responsible to the principal for the acts or negligence of the agent so`
  line selected.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A instructs B, a merchant, to buy a ship for him. B employs a ship-surveyor of good reputation to choose a ship for A.`
  line `The surveyor makes the choice negligently and the ship turns out to be unseaworthy and is lost. B is not, but the surveyor is,`
  line `responsible to A.`
  line
  line `(b) A consigns goods to B, a merchant, for sale. B, in due course, employs an auctioneer in good credit to sell the goods of`
  line `A, and allows the auctioneer to receive the proceeds of the sale. The auctioneer afterwards becomes insolvent without having`
  line `accounted for the proceeds. B is not responsible to A for the proceeds.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (38753)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 198
  title `Right of person as to acts done for him without his authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38753&sectionno=196&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `Where acts are done by one person on behalf of another, but without his knowledge or authority, he may`
  line `elect to ratify or to disown such acts. If he ratify them, the same effects will follow as if they had been`
  line `performed by his authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (38754)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 199
  title `Ratification may be expressed or implied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38754&sectionno=197&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `Ratification may be expressed or may be implied`
  line `in the conduct of the person on whose behalf the acts are done.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, without authority, buys goods for B. Afterwards B sells them to C on his own account; B's conduct implies a`
  line `ratification of the purchase made for him by A.`
  line
  line `(b) A, without B's authority, lends B's money to C. Afterwards B accepts interest on the money from C. B's conduct implies`
  line `a ratification of the loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (38755)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 200
  title `Knowledge requisite for valid ratification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38755&sectionno=198&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `No valid ratification can be made by a person`
  line `whose knowledge of the facts of the case is materially defective.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (38756)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 201
  title `Effect of ratifying unauthorized act forming part of a transaction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38756&sectionno=199&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `A person ratifying any`
  line `unauthorized act done on his behalf ratifies the whole of the transaction of which such act formed a part.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (38757)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 202
  title `Ratification of unauthorized act cannot injure third person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38757&sectionno=200&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `An act done by one person on`
  line `behalf of another, without such other persons authority, which, if done with authority, would have the`
  line `effect of subjecting a third person to damages, or of terminating any right or interest of a third person,`
  line `cannot, by ratification, be made to have such effect.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, not being authorized thereto by B, demands, on behalf of B, the delivery of a chattel, the property of B, from C, who`
  line `is in possession of it. This demand cannot be ratified by B, so as to make C liable for damages for his refusal to deliver.`
  line
  line `(b) A holds a lease from B, terminable on three months' notice. C, an unauthorized person, gives notice of termination to A.`
  line `The notice cannot be ratified by B, so as to be binding on A.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (38758)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 203
  title `Termination of agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38758&sectionno=201&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `An agency is terminated by the principal revoking his authority; or`
  line `by the agent renouncing the business of the agency; or by the business of the agency being completed; or`
  line `by either the principal or agent dying or becoming of unsound mind; or by the principal being adjudicated`
  line `an insolvent under the provisions of any Act for the time being in force for the relief of insolvent debtors.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (38759)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 204
  title `Termination of agency, where agent has an interest in subject-matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38759&sectionno=202&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `Where the agent has`
  line `himself an interest in the property which forms the subject-matter of the agency, the agency cannot, in the`
  line `absence of an express contract, be terminated to the prejudice of such interest.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A gives authority to B to sell A's land, and to pay himself, out of the proceeds, the debts due to him from A. A cannot`
  line `revoke this authority, nor can it be terminated by his insanity or death.`
  line
  line `(b) A consigns 1,000 bales of cotton to B, who has made advances to him on such cotton, and desires B to sell the cotton,`
  line `and to repay himself out of the price, the amount of his own advances. A cannot revoke this authority, nor is it terminated by his`
  line `insanity or death.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (38760)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 205
  title `When principal may revoke agent's authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38760&sectionno=203&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `The principal may, save as is otherwise`
  line `provided by the last preceding section, revoke the authority given to his agent at any time before the`
  line `authority has been exercised so as to bind the principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (38761)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 206
  title `Revocation where authority has been partly exercised.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38761&sectionno=204&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `The principal cannot revoke the`
  line `authority given to his agent after the authority has been partly exercised, so far as regards such acts and`
  line `obligations as arise from acts already done in the agency.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A authorizes B to buy 1,000 bales of cotton on account of A, and to pay for it out of A's moneys remaining in B‟s hands.`
  line `B buys 1,000 bales of cotton in his own name, so as to make himself personally liable for the price. A cannot revoke B's`
  line `authority so far as regards payment for the cotton.`
  line
  line `(b) A authorizes B to buy 1,000 bales of cotton on account of A, and to pay for it out of A's moneys remaining in B's hands.`
  line `B buys 1,000 bales of cotton in A's name, and so as not to render himself personally liable for the price. A can revoke B's`
  line `authority to pay for the cotton.`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (38762)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 207
  title `Compensation for revocation by principal, or renunciation by agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38762&sectionno=205&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `Where there is an`
  line `express or implied contract that the agency should be continued for any period of time, the principal must`
  line `make compensation to the agent, or the agent to the principal, as the case may be, for any previous`
  line `revocation or renunciation of the agency without sufficient cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (38763)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 208
  title `Notice of revocation or renunciation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38763&sectionno=206&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `Reasonable notice must be given of such revocation or`
  line `renunciation, otherwise the damage thereby resulting to the principal or the agent, as the case may be,`
  line `must be made good to the one by the other.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (38764)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 209
  title `Revocation and renunciation may be expressed or implied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38764&sectionno=207&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `Revocation and renunciation`
  line `may be expressed or may be implied in the conduct of the principal or agent respectively.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A empowers B to let A's house. Afterwards A lets it himself. This is an implied revocation of`
  line `B's authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (38765)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 210
  title `When termination of agent's authority takes effect as to agent, and as to third persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38765&sectionno=208&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `The termination of the authority of an agent does not, so far as regards the agent, take effect before it`
  line `becomes known to him, or, so far as regards third persons, before it becomes known to them.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A directs B to sell goods for him, and agrees to give B five per cent. commission on the price fetched by the goods. A`
  line `afterwards, by letter, revoke B's authority. B, after the letter is sent, but before he receives it, sells the goods for 100 rupees. The`
  line `sale is binding on A, and B is entitled to five rupees as his commission.`
  line
  line `(b) A, at Madras, by letter, directs B to sell for him some cotton lying in a warehouse in Bombay, and afterwards, by letter,`
  line `revokes his authority to sell, and directs B to send the cotton to Madras. B, after receiving the second letter, enters into a contract`
  line `with C, who knows of the first letter, but not of the second, for the sale to him of the cotton. C pays B the money, with which B`
  line `absconds. C's payment is good as against A.`
  line
  line `(c) A directs B, his agent, to pay certain money to C. A dies, and D takes out probate to his will. B, after A's death, but`
  line `before hearing of it, pays the money to C. The payment is good as against D, the executor.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (38766)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 211
  title `Agent's duty on termination of agency by principal's death or insanity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38766&sectionno=209&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `When an agency`
  line `is terminated by the principal dying or becoming of unsound mind, the agent is bound to take, on behalf`
  line `of the representatives of his late principal, all reasonable steps for the protection and preservation of the`
  line `interests entrusted to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (38767)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 212
  title `Termination of sub-agent's authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38767&sectionno=210&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `The termination of the authority of an agent causes`
  line `the termination (subject to the rules herein contained regarding the termination of an agent's authority) of`
  line `the authority of all sub-agents appointed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (38768)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 213
  title `Agent's duty in conducting principal's business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38768&sectionno=211&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `An agent is bound to conduct the business`
  line `of his principal according to the directions given by the principal, or, in the absence of any such`
  line `directions, according to the custom which prevails in doing business of the same kind at the place where`
  line `the agent conducts such business. When the agent acts otherwise, if any loss be sustained, he must make it`
  line `good to his principal, and if any profit accrues, he must account for it.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, an agent engaged in carrying on for B a business, in which it is the custom to invest from time to time, at interest, the`
  line `moneys which may be in hand, omits to make such investment. A must make good to B the interest usually obtained by such`
  line investments.
  line
  line `(b) B, a broker, in whose business it is not the custom to sell on credit, sells goods of A on credit to C, whose credit at the`
  line `time was very high. C, before payment, becomes insolvent. B must make good the loss to A.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (38769)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 214
  title `Skill and diligence required from agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38769&sectionno=212&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `An agent is bound to conduct the business of the`
  line `agency with as much skill as is generally possessed by persons engaged in similar business unless the`
  line `principal has notice of his want of skill. The agent is always bound to act with reasonable diligence, and`
  line `to use such skill as he possesses; and to make compensation to his principal in respect of the direct`
  line `consequences of his own neglect, want of skill or misconduct, but not in respect of loss or damage which`
  line `are indirectly or remotely caused by such neglect, want of skill, or misconduct.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, a merchant in Calcutta, has an agent, B, in London, to whom a sum of money is paid on A's account, with orders to`
  line `remit. B retains the money for a considerable time. A, in consequence of not receiving the money, becomes insolvent. B is liable`
  line `for the money and interest from the day on which it ought to have been paid, according to the usual rate, and for any further`
  line `direct loss-as, e.g., by variation of rate of exchange-but not further.`
  line
  line `(b) A, an agent for the sale of goods, having authority to sell on credit, sells to B on credit, without making the proper and`
  line `usual enquiries as to the solvency of B. B, at the time of such sale, is insolvent. A must make compensation to his principal in`
  line `respect of any loss thereby sustained.`
  line
  line `(c) A, an insurance-broker employed by B to effect an insurance on a ship, omits to see that the usual clauses are inserted in`
  line `the policy. The ship is after wards lost. In consequence of the omission of the clauses nothing can be recovered from the`
  line `underwriters. A is bound to make good the loss to B.`
  line
  line `(d) A, a merchant in England, directs B, his agent at Bombay, who accepts the agency, to send him 100 bales of cotton by a`
  line `certain ship. B, having it in his power to send the cotton, omits to do so. The ship arrives safely in England. Soon after her arrival`
  line `the price of cotton rises. B is bound to make good to A the profit which he might have made by the 100 bales of cotton at the time`
  line `the ship arrived, but not any profit he might have made by the subsequent rise.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (38770)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 215
  title `Agent's accounts.`
  content `An agent is bound to render proper accounts to his principal on demand.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38770&sectionno=213&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (38771)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 216
  title `Agent's duty to communicate with principal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38771&sectionno=214&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `It is the duty of an agent, in cases of difficulty,`
  line `to use all reasonable diligence in communicating with his principal, and in seeking to obtain his`
  line instructions.
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (42840)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 217
  title `Right of principal when agent deals, on his own account, in business of agency without principals consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=42840&sectionno=215&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `If an agent deals on his own account in the business of the agency, without first`
  line `obtaining the consent of his principal and acquainting him with all material circumstances which have`
  line `come to his own knowledge on the subject, the principal may repudiate the transaction, if the case shows,`
  line `either that any material fact has been dishonestly concealed from him by the agent, or that the dealings of`
  line `the agent have been disadvantageous to him.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A directs B to sell A's estate. B buys the estate for himself in the name of C. A, on discovering that B has bought the`
  line `estate for himself, may repudiate the sale, if he can show that B has dishonestly concealed any material fact, or that the sale has`
  line `been disadvantageous to him.`
  line
  line `(b) A directs B to sell A's estate B, on looking over the estate before selling it, finds a mine on the estate which is unknown`
  line `to A. B informs A that he wishes to buy the estate for himself, but conceals the discovery of the mine. A allows B to buy, in`
  line `ignorance of the existence of the mine. A, on discovering that B knew of the mine at the time he bought the estate, may either`
  line `repudiate or adopt the sale at his option.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (38773)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 218
  title `Principal's right to benefit gained by agent dealing on his own account in business of agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38773&sectionno=216&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `If an agent, without the knowledge of his principal, deals in the business of the agency on his`
  line `own account instead of on account of his principal, the principal is entitled to claim from the agent any`
  line `benefit which may have resulted to him from the transaction.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A directs B, his agent, to buy a certain house for him. B tells A it cannot be bought, and buys the house for himself. A may,`
  line `on discovering that B has bought the house, compel him to sell it to A at the price he gave for it.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (38774)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 219
  title `Agent's right of retainer out of sums received on principal's account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38774&sectionno=217&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `An agent may retain,`
  line `out of any sums received on account of the principal in the business of the agency, all moneys due to`
  line `himself in respect of advances made or expenses properly incurred by him in conducting such business,`
  line `and also such remuneration as may be payable to him for acting as agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (38775)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 220
  title `Agent's duty to pay sums received for principal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38775&sectionno=218&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such deductions, the agent is`
  line `bound to pay to his principal all sums received on his account.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (38776)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 221
  title `When agent's remuneration becomes due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38776&sectionno=219&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of any special contract, payment`
  line `for the performance of any act is not due to the agent until the completion of such act; but an agent may`
  line `detain moneys received by him on account of goods sold, although the whole of the goods consigned to`
  line `him for sale may not have been sold, or although the sale may not be actually complete.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (38777)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 222
  title `Agent not entitled to remuneration for business misconducted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38777&sectionno=220&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `An agent who is guilty of`
  line `misconduct in the business of the agency, is not entitled to any remuneration in respect of that part of the`
  line `business which he has misconducted.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A employs B to recover, 1,00,000 rupees from C, and to lay it out on good security. B recovers the 1,00,000 rupees; and`
  line `lays out 90,000 rupees on good security, but lays out 10,000 rupees on security which he ought to have known to be bad,`
  line `whereby A loses 2,000 rupees. B is entitled to remuneration for recovering the 1,00,000 rupees and for investing the 90,000`
  line `rupees. He is not entitled to any remuneration for investing the 10,000 rupees, and he must make good the 2,000 rupees to B.`
  line
  line `(b) A employs B to recover 1,000 rupees from C. Through B's misconduct the money is not recovered. B is entitled to no`
  line `remuneration for his services, and must make good the loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (38778)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 223
  title `Agent's lien on principal's property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38778&sectionno=221&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of any contract to the contrary, an agent`
  line `is entitled to retain goods, papers and other property, whether movable or immovable of the principal`
  line `received by him, until the amount due to himself for commission, disbursements and services in respect`
  line `of the same has been paid or accounted for to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (38779)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 224
  title `Agent to be indemnified against consequences of lawful acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38779&sectionno=222&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `The employer of an agent is`
  line `bound to indemnify him against the consequences of all lawful acts done by such agent in exercise of the`
  line `authority conferred upon him.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) B, at Singapur, under instructions from A of Calcutta, contracts with C to deliver certain goods to him. A does not send`
  line `the goods to B, and C sues B for breach of contract. B informs A of the suit, and A authorizes him to defend the suit. B defends`
  line `the suit, and is compelled to pay damages and costs, and incurs expenses. A is liable to B for such damages, costs and expenses.`
  line
  line `(b) B, a broker at Calcutta, by the orders of A, a merchant there, contracts with C for the purchase of 10 casks of oil for A.`
  line `Afterwards A refuses to receive the oil, and C sues B. B informs A, who repudiates the contract altogether. B defends, but`
  line `unsuccessfully, and has to pay damages and costs and incurs expenses. A is liable to B for such damages, costs and expenses.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (38780)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 225
  title `Agent to be indemnified against consequences of acts done in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38780&sectionno=223&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `Where one`
  line `person employs another to do an act, and the agent does the act in good faith, the employer is liable to`
  line `indemnify the agent against the consequences of that act, though it cause an injury to the rights of third`
  line persons.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, a decree-holder and entitled to execution of B's goods, requires the officer of the Court to seize certain goods,`
  line `representing them to be the goods of B. The officer seizes the goods, and is sued by C, the true owner of the goods. A is liable to`
  line `indemnify the officer for the sum which he is compelled to pay to C, in consequence of obeying A's directions.`
  line
  line `(b) B, at the request of A, sells goods in the possession of A, but which A had no right to dispose of, B does not know this,`
  line `and hands over the proceeds of the sale to A. Afterwards C, the true owner of the goods, sues B and recovers the value of the`
  line `goods and costs. A is liable to indemnify B for what he has been compelled to pay to C, and for B's own expenses.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (38781)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 226
  title `Non-liability of employer of agent to do a criminal act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes `1. See s. 24, supra.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38781&sectionno=224&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `Where one person employs another`
  line `to do an act which is criminal, the employer is not liable to the agent, either upon an express or an implied`
  line `promise, to indemnify him against the consequences of that Act^1`
  line .
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A employs B to beat C, and agrees to indemnify him against all consequences of the act. B thereupon beats C, and has to`
  line `pay damages to C for so doing. A is not liable to indemnify B for those damages.`
  line
  line `(b) B, the proprietor of a newspaper, publishes, at As request, a libel upon C in the paper, and A agrees to indemnify B`
  line `against the consequences of the publication, and all costs and damages of any action in respect thereof. B is sued by C and has to`
  line `pay damages, and also incurs expenses. A is not liable to B upon the indemnity.`
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (38782)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 227
  title `Compensation to agent for injury caused by principal's neglect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes `1. Cf. the Indian Fatal Accidents Act, 1855 (13 of 1855).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38782&sectionno=225&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `The principal must make`
  line `compensation to his agent in respect of injury^1`
  line `caused to such agent by the principal's neglect or want of`
  line skill.
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A employs B as a bricklayer in building a house, and puts up the scaffolding himself. The scaffolding is unskilfully put up,`
  line `and B is in consequence hurt. A must make compensation to B.`
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (38783)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 228
  title `Enforcement and consequences of agent's contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38783&sectionno=226&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line `Contracts entered into through an`
  line `agent, and obligations arising from acts done by an agent, may be enforced in the same manner, and will`
  line `have the same legal consequences, as if the contracts had been entered into and the acts done by the`
  line `principal in person.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A buys goods from B, knowing that he is an agent for their sale, but not knowing who is the principal. B's principal is`
  line `the person entitled to claim from A the price of the goods, and A cannot, in a. suit by the principal, set-off against that claim a`
  line `debt due to himself from B.`
  line
  line `(b) A, being B's agent with authority to receive money on his behalf, receives from C a sum of money due to B. C is`
  line `discharged of his obligation to pay the sum in question to B.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (38784)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 229
  title `Principal how far bound, when agent exceeds authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38784&sectionno=227&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `When an agent does more than he`
  line `is authorized to do, and when the part of what he does, which is within his authority, can be separated`
  line `from the part which is beyond his authority, so much only of what he does as is within his authority is`
  line `binding as between him and his principal.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A, being owner of a ship and cargo, authorizes B to procure an insurance for 4,000 rupees on the ship. B procures a policy`
  line `for 4,000 rupees on the ship, and another for the like sum on the cargo. A is bound to pay the premium for the policy on the ship,`
  line `but not the premium for the policy on the cargo.`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (38785)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 230
  title `Principal not bound when excess of agent's authority is not separable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38785&sectionno=228&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `Where an agent`
  line `does more than he is authorized to do, and what he does beyond the scope of his authority cannot be`
  line `separated from what is within it, the principal is not bound to recognize the transaction.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A authorizes B to buy 500 sheep for him. B buys 500 sheep and 200 lambs for one sum of 6,000 rupees. A may repudiate`
  line `the whole transaction.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (38786)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 231
  title `Consequences of notice given to agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38786&sectionno=229&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `Any notice given to or information obtained by the`
  line `agent, provided it be given or obtained in the course of the business transacted by him for the principal,`
  line `shall, as between the principal and third parties, have the same legal consequences as if it had been given`
  line `to or obtained by the principal.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A is employed by B to buy from C certain goods, of which C is the apparent owner, and buys them accordingly. In the`
  line `course of the treaty for the sale, A learns that the goods really belonged to D, but B is ignorant of that fact. B is not entitled to`
  line `set-off a debt owing to him from C against the price of the goods.`
  line
  line `(b) A is employed by B to buy from C goods of which C is the apparent owner. A was, before he was so employed, a servant`
  line `of C, and then learnt that the goods really belonged to D, but B is ignorant of that fact. In spite of the knowledge of his agent, B`
  line `may set-off against the price of the goods a debt owing to him from C.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (38787)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 232
  title `Agent cannot personally enforce, nor be bound by, contracts on behalf of principal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38787&sectionno=230&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `n the`
  line `absence of any contract to that effect, an agent cannot personally enforce contracts entered into by him on`
  line `behalf of his principal, nor is he personally bound by them.`
  line
  line `Presumption of contract to contrary—Such a contract shall be presumed to exist in the following`
  line `cases:—`
  line
  line `(1) where the contract is made by an agent for the sale or purchase of goods for a merchant`
  line `resident abroad;`
  line
  line `(2) where the agent does not disclose the name of his principal;`
  line
  line `(3) where the principal, though disclosed, cannot be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (38788)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 233
  title `Rights of parties to a contract made by agent not disclosed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38788&sectionno=231&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `If an agent makes a contract`
  line `with a person who neither knows, nor has reason to suspect, that he is an agent, his principal may require`
  line `the performance of the contract; but the other contracting party has, as against the principal, the same`
  line `rights as he would have had as against the agent if the agent had been principal.`
  line
  line `If the principal discloses himself before the contract is completed, the other contracting party may`
  line `refuse to fulfil the contract, if he can show that, if he had known who was the principal in the contract, or`
  line `if he had known that the agent was not a principal, he would not have entered into the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (38789)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 234
  title `Performance of contract with agent supposed to be principal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38789&sectionno=232&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `Where one man makes a`
  line `contract with another, neither knowing nor having reasonable ground to suspect that the other is an agent,`
  line `the principal, if he requires the performance of the contract, can only obtain such performance subject to`
  line `the rights and obligations subsisting between the agent and the other party to the contract.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A, who owes 500 rupees to B, sells 1,000 rupees worth of rice to B. A is acting as agent for C in the transaction, but B has`
  line `no knowledge nor reasonable ground of suspicion that such is the case. C cannot compel B to take the rice without allowing him`
  line `to set-off A's debt.`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (38790)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 235
  title `Right of person dealing with agent personally liable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38790&sectionno=233&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `In cases where the agent is personally`
  line `liable, a person dealing with him may hold either him or his principal, or both of them, liable.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A enters into a contract with B to sell him 100 bales of cotton, and afterwards discovers that B was acting as agent for C. A`
  line `may sue either B or C, or both, for the price of the cotton.`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (42841)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 236
  title `Consequence of inducing agent or principal to act on belief that principal or agent will be held exclusively liable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=42841&sectionno=234&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `When a person who has made a contract with an agent induces the agent to act`
  line `upon the belief that the principal only will be held liable, or induces the principal to act upon the belief`
  line `that the agent only will be held liable, he cannot afterwards hold liable the agent or principal respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (38792)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 237
  title `Liability of pretended agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38792&sectionno=235&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `A person untruly representing himself to be the authorized`
  line `agent of another, and thereby inducing a third person to deal with him as such agent, is liable, if his`
  line `alleged employer does not ratify his acts, to make compensation to the other in respect of any loss or`
  line `damage which he has incurred by so dealing.`
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (38793)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 238
  title `Person falsely contracting as agent, not entitled to performance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38793&sectionno=236&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `A person with whom a`
  line `contract has been entered into in the character of agent, is not entitled to require the performance of it, if`
  line `he was in reality acting, not as agent, but on his own account.`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (38794)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 239
  title `Liability of principal inducing belief that agent's unauthorized acts were authorized.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38794&sectionno=237&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line `When an agent has, without authority, done acts or incurred obligations to third persons on behalf of his`
  line `principal, the principal is bound by such acts or obligations, if he has by his words or conduct induced`
  line `such third persons to believe that such acts and obligations were within the scope of the agent's authority.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A consigns goods to B for sale, and gives him instructions not to sell under a fixed price. C, being ignorant of Bs`
  line `instructions, enters into a contract with B to buy the goods at a price lower than the reserved price. A is bound by the contract.`
  line
  line `(b) A entrusts B with negotiable instruments endorsed in blank. B sells them to C in violation of private orders from A. The`
  line `sale is good.`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (38795)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 240
  title `Effect, on agreement, of misrepresentation or fraud by agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=38795&sectionno=238&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `Misrepresentation made, or`
  line `frauds committed, by agents acting in the course of their business for their principals, have the same`
  line `effect on agreements made by such agents as if such misrepresentations or frauds had been made or`
  line `committed by the principals; but misrepresentations made, or frauds committed, by agents, in matters`
  line `which do not fall within their authority, do not affect their principals.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, being B's agent for the sale of goods, induces C to buy them by a misrepresentation, which he was not authorized by`
  line `B to make. The contract is voidable, as between B and C, at the option of C.`
  line
  line `(b) A, the captain of B's ship, signs bills of lading without having received on board the goods mentioned therein. The bills`
  line `of lading are void as between B and the pretended cosignor.`
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (44452)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 241
  title Repealed..
  content `['Partnership' defined.] Rep. by s. 73 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=44452&sectionno=239&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  sectionId (44453)
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 242
  title Repealed..
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=44453&sectionno=240&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `[Lender not a partner by advancing money for share of profits.] Rep. by s. 73 and the Second`
  line `Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (45451)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 243
  title Repealed..
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=45451&sectionno=241&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `[Property left in business by retiring partner, or decreased partner's preventative.] Rep. by s. 73`
  line `and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (45452)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 244
  title Repealed..
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428&sectionId=45452&sectionno=242&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00035_187209_1523268996428
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `[Servant or agent remunerated by share of profits, not a partner.] Rep. by s. 73 and the Second`
  line `Schedule, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_243:
  sectionId (45453)
  sectionNo (243)
  orderNo 245
  title Repealed..
